groupDetail.label: Exposure to different types of natural disasters varies by region across Canada
groupDetail.description:
Multi-hazard exposure index, by forward sortation area

Multi hazard exposure

5-High exposure to 3 or more disasters

4-High exposure to 2 disastersn

3-High exposure to 1 disaster

2-Medium exposure to 1 or more disasters

1-Low exposure to all disasters

Clusters

A-Higher exposure to disasters and higher indebtedness

B-Moderate exposure to disasters and limited access to credit

C-Lower exposure to disasters and lower financial vulenrabilities

Sources: Canadian Disaster Database and Bank of Canada calculations
